### Overview
This project is a Node.js application that automates email responses and labeling in Gmail. It checks for new emails, sends an auto-reply to those without previous responses, and applies customizable labels for easy organization.

## Folder Structure

- **app.js:** Main entry point for the application.
- **gmail.js:** Module containing functions related to Gmail API interactions.
- **auth.js:** Module handling authentication and credentials setup.
- **package.json:** File containing project metadata and dependencies.

## Prerequisites

- Gmail API credentials from the [Google Developer Console](https://console.developers.google.com/).

## Setup

1. Clone the repository:
   git clone https://github.com/YbiG-blog/openinapp_backend_assignment_yash_vardhan.git

2. npm install

# Set up Gmail API credentials:

Go to the Google Developer Console.
Create a new project and enable the Gmail API.
Create OAuth 2.0 credentials (download as credentials.json) and save in the project root.
Run the application to generate token.json for authentication.

# Start the application:
 nodemon app.js or node app.js

## Usage
The application will automatically check for new emails, send auto-replies, and categorize emails using labels.